libburn
------------------------------------------
Libburn is a library by which preformatted data get onto optical media:
CD, DVD and BD (Blu-Ray). It also offers a facility for reading data
blocks from its drives without using the normal block device I/O, which
has advantages and disadvantages. It seems appropriate, nevertheless,
to do writing and reading via same channel. On several Linux systems,
the block device driver needs reloading of the drive tray in order to
make available freshly written data. The libburn read function does not
need such a reload. The code of libburn is independent of cdrecord.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.0.2-1
  cygwin-devel-2.0.2-1
  libburn-devel-1.4.0-1bl1
  libburn4-1.4.0-1bl1
  libcdio16-0.93-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-2
  cygport-0.19.0-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-3
  libtool-2.4.6-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://libburnia-project.org/

Canonical download:
  http://files.libburnia-project.org/releases/libburn-1.4.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libburn-1.4.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libburn-1.4.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libburn-1.4.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libburn-1.4.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libburn4-1.4.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libburn-devel-1.4.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libburn)
  /usr/bin/cdrskin.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libburn.README
  /usr/share/doc/libburn/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libburn/CONTRIBUTORS
  /usr/share/doc/libburn/COPYING
